<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;line-height:200%'>(b) &amp; (c):<span
style='mso-tab-count:1'>            </span>Analysis indicates that most of the
suicide attacks are being carried out by Foreign Mercenaries (FM) dominated
terrorist outfits bases across the border. Suicide attacks on security forces
posts/establishment are known facets of the modus operandi of terrorists.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>The timing and place of occurrence of such
attacks as well as ever changing hideouts have inbuilt element of surprise and,
therefore, cannot always be anticipated.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Security measures for countering suicide attacks have been enhanced to
meet effectively similar eventualities in the future.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;line-height:200%'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;line-height:200%'><span
style='mso-tab-count:1'>            </span>Government have called upon Pakistan
to put an end to cross border infiltration and permanently dismantle the
infrastructure of support to terrorism in that country.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal align=right style='text-align:right;line-height:200%'>2/---</p>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center;line-height:200%'>-2-</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;line-height:200%'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-indent:.5in;line-height:200%'>President
Musharraf of Pakistan had in the Joint Press Statement of January 6, 2004
reassured that he would not permit any territory under Pakistans control to be
used to support terrorism in any manner.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>However, Pakistan has so far not taken any credible steps to dismantle
the infrastructure of support to terrorism in that country on a permanent
basis.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Our concerns about the
continuing existence of infrastructure of support to terrorism were made known
to Pakistan during the Foreign Secretary level talks held in New Delhi on June
27-28,2004 and again during the Home Secretary level talks with Pakistan held
in Islamabad on August 10-11,2004.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;line-height:200%'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;line-height:200%'><span
style='mso-tab-count:1'>            </span>Besides diplomatic efforts,
Government, Jointly with the State Government, have adopted a multi-pronged
approach, to contain cross-border infiltration particularly in J&amp;K, which
includes, inter-alia, strengthening of border management and multi-tiered and
multi-modal deployment along the International Border/LOC and near the ever
changing infiltration routes, construction of Border fencing, improved
technology, weapons and equipment for security forces, improved intelligence
and operational coordination and synergising intelligence flow to check
infiltration, as well as coordinated counter terrorism measures.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>The counter infiltration efforts are
reviewed from time to time.</p>

